<br>
- Is it better to sell items that you make back to the merchants or salvage the material?<br>
<br>
- Is Gna Faste the only place that sells the highest level materials (i.e. asterrite, ebonwood)? Haggerfel sells stonewood and adamantium but not the next level.<br>
<br>
- What's the best way to advance after 650?<br>
<br>
- What is the limit of your primary skill? I once heard 850, but I see Jens has his armorcraft already beyond that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kailikor>kailikor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(1/8/02 4:52:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crafting questions</span><hr size=1> Ok, I've already answered my question about whether it's better to sell crafted items back to the merchants or to salvage them. Here's what I found.<br>
<br>
Stonewood Great Composite Bow<br>
Cost - 23g 6s 88c<br>
Sell to merchants - 17g 28s<br>
Salvage (16 stonewood boards) - 10g 36s 80c<br>
<br>
So in this example, you loose 25% by selling back to the merchants and 55% by salvaging. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kailikor>kailikor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(1/8/02 6:18:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crafting questions</span><hr size=1> Ok, I just burned 120 gold to raise my fletching from 651 to 654. There has got to be a better way to raise skills after 650.<br>
<br>
Jens? Anyone else with skills higher than 650 care to comment? I'm guessing weapon and armorcrafters have an easy time doing consignments. Very few ever want fletching items made <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
However, I did make a runewood bow tonight that is a masterpiece (100% quality). It was my first <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ushataramaclear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shatara MacLear</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(1/8/02 10:01:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.premiernet.net/~chandler/images/vixen.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crafting questions</span><hr size=1> My experience is: raising skill over 650 = spending alot of cash.<br>
<br>
You can try to make items to sell for a profit to players but I find that to be very time consuming (if you have a rep some people will search you out with a /tell - this only happens when you are fighting in Emain though hehe).  The market for selling the high end items is very small.  So you sell to guild members at cost and sell back to vendors for huge losses per item.<br>
<br>
That's the way the game works.  &lt;shrugs&gt;<br>
<br>
-Alfdis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/utorgeirr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torgeirr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Councellor</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(1/8/02 12:50:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crafting questions</span><hr size=1> &gt; That's the way the game works. &lt;shrugs&gt;<br>
<br>
We can only hope that spellcrafting will energize high-end crafting.  Until then, going post-650 on fletching and weapons appears to be mainly for your own satisfaction.  I don't know for sure, but I imagine that the L40 quest line pretty well killed off any market for high-end weapons.<br>
               -- Gisli<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/utabot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tabot</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Councellor</span><br>  Posts: 255<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(1/8/02 9:25:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crafting questions</span><hr size=1> Suprisingly enough, post-650 to 675ish Tailoring is not a killer to do... I was working with three (and a fourth at one time) armorsmiths nearing the end of their consignments, yet managed to gain 9 skill points (to 659) doing so. I imagine it will slow down more (took 5 hours for those nine because most of what they needed was green to me to make) once they only need leathers for specific orders from players though... <p>Ohlar, Skald of Siol Lear<BR>Harl, Runemaster and Tailor of Siol Lear</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uonahoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Onahoo</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(1/10/02 5:20:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crafting questions</span><hr size=1> If you armorcraft with a tailor, it costs about 15-25 gp per skill point, not including any profit for the tailor.  Weaponcrafting I know takes about 50gp per skill point, which is about what armor would cost if you consider the store markup price for leather.<br>
<br>
I'd say I spent about 7000 gp powerskilling from 650 to 876 in armorcrafting, and I'd guess it would be about double that for weaponcrafting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uonahoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Onahoo</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(1/10/02 5:23:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crafting questions</span><hr size=1> 2 notes I should probably add... I did consignments before the nerf, so I had about 1600gp when I hit 650 skill just for consignments, and I would say I made about 4000gp farming asterite before the /salvage nerf. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kailikor>kailikor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(1/11/02 7:08:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crafting questions</span><hr size=1> Wow! That's a lot of gold. Ok, I heard someone in game mention the crafting nerf, but I'm not quiet sure what it entailed. Could someone enlighten me?<br>
<br>
I was up to about 250g by the time I had hit 650 in Fletching. I guess I spent a fare amount on better armor and weapons along the way. However, I definitely would have never made 1600g. Maybe doing tasks for the Fletching master didn't pay as well as tasks for the other masters? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kailikor>kailikor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(1/12/02 5:23:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crafting questions</span><hr size=1> Ok, another question. According to Mythic,<br>
<br>
&quot;Trade skills - material types - the two highest material types are intended to be added by the end of January. Note on January 11 - it's looking like this date will be pushed back a bit. I'll update this note again when I have more information.&quot;<br>
<br>
So will this mean that the masters will be modified to give out tasks until say 850? Otherwise, how would one ever advance to use the two highest material types? Heck, I can't even use Ebonwood yet. That would require my fletching to be 700+. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uonahoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Onahoo</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(1/13/02 12:42:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crafting questions</span><hr size=1> Consignments were giving ~5% too much gold, so profits were around 10% instead of 5%.  So basically, they cut profits by about 40-60%.<br>
<br>
I only did consignments from 500 to 650, and had 1600 or so gp at the end... having a tailor to save costs on armor really helped that though.<br>
<br>
Also, they've stated they may add quests for crafters to help them raise skill 650+, but they would be the sorts of things that require you to travel all over the realm (outside of Jordheim) and take lots of time.<br>
<br>
Time is actually a much bigger problem than money 40+. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showPrevMessage?topicID=11.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showNextMessage?topicID=11.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.emailToFriend?topicID=11.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.threadControl?topicID=11.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm11.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub5.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="theclanmacleargeneral">The Great Hall<option value="theclanmaclearfrm8">Inner Court<option value="theclanmaclearfrm6">Events<option value="theclanmaclearfrm5">Provisioner's Square<option value="theclanmaclearfrm4">Chief's Council Chambers<opti